The paper proposes a deep learning approach for translating natural language expressions into SPARQL queries, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and knowledge representation (KR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, particularly deep learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with Linked Data and DBpedia, which are related to databases and information retrieval (IR), indicating that it could belong to cs.DB and cs.IR sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for question answering, which involves modeling and optimization, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning).
